import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { View, TouchableOpacity, TextInput, Alert, SafeAreaView } from 'react-native';
import Lista from '../../components/Lista/Lista';
import estiloColecao from './estiloColecao';
import { MaterialIcons } from '@expo/vector-icons'
import { AntDesign } from '@expo/vector-icons'
import useFormal from '@kevinwolf/formal-native'
import {Button, Input, Text} from 'react-native-elements'
import * as yup from 'yup'

function Colecao({ navigation, route }) {
const schema = yup.object().shape({
  Username: yup
    .string() // check if it's a string
    .required(), // compulsory field, can't omit it
  Email: yup
    .string()
    .email('Invalid Email Address') // check if it's a valid email or else print the error 'Invalid Email Address'
    .required(),
  Password: yup
    .string()
    .min(4) // minimum length can be 4
    .max(32) // maximum length can be 32
    .required(),
  'Confirm Password': yup
    .string()
    .oneOf([yup.ref('Password'), null], "Passwords don't match") // check if it matches with 'Password' or is null; otherwise print the error 'Passwords don't match'
    .required(),
})
const initialValues = {
  Username: 'tonystark',
  Email: 'tonystark@avengers.io',
  Password: 'avengers',
  'Confirm Password': 'avengers',
}
const voltar = () => {
        navigation.navigate('Inicial')
    }
const formal = useFormal(initialValues, {
    schema,
    onSubmit: values => Alert.alert(JSON.stringify(values))
  })
return (
<View style={estiloColecao.container}>

	<View style={estiloColecao.header}>
		<TouchableOpacity onPress={voltar}>
			<MaterialIcons name="arrow-back" size={24} color="#fff" />
		</TouchableOpacity>
		<Text style={estiloColecao.texto}>Contato</Text>
	</View>
	
	<View style={estiloColecao.formulario}>
        <SafeAreaView>
      <View style={styles.space}>
        <Text h1>Formal</Text>
      </View>
    </SafeAreaView>
	</View>
</View>
)
}

export default Colecao;
